# 2. 楽しみな理由は？

Kohane: Hmm...
An: How's it going, Kohane? Find anything good?
Kohane: *Nod* I'm trying to decide which to choose. I didn't realize they made so many different kinds of ski gloves.
Toya: Yes. There are three-fingered gloves and mittens... But you may want to buy a pair of five-fingered gloves, since our plan is to become better skiers this time.
Akito: Yeah, and they also might be easier to wear since they're the most like normal gloves.
Kohane: Then, I'll get a pair of those. As for what color—
???: <Hello, everyone. How's your shopping coming along?>
An: Hi, Luka! Oh, you're all here!
Len: <Because we heard that you guys are gonna go skiing again. And we had to come since it's always fun to go shopping!>
Toya: Yes, I see. We were just shopping for gloves.
KAITO: <Oh, I didn't realize that ski gloves came in such a huge variety.>
Rin: <Yeah, wow! Look at all the different types and colors. And the designs for some of these are so cute. I wouldn't know which to choose!>
An: Haha. Kohane said the exact same thing!
KAITO: <Still, another skiing trip... You all did seem to have quite a lot of fun the last time you went!>
Akito: Yeah, we did. But Toya really took us by surprise when he said he wanted to go again.
Luka: <Wait, Toya, this was your idea? I was under the impression that it was An or Akito's.>
Toya: Yes, since I learned to ski on my own last time, albeit very briefly. That's why I'd like to go again.
Toya: Also, the snowball fight we had was very fun.
Toya: Unfortunately, I'm still not sure if I'll be able to ride the ski lift...
Akito: You don't have to if you don't want to, dude.
Kohane: Hehe. We can walk up the slope again together.
Kohane: I'm actually also really excited about this trip...!
An: Because skiing isn't the only thing Kohane's looking forward to.
KAITO: <Wait, what's she talking about?!>
Kohane: Hehe. I am looking forward to skiing, but during this trip...
Kohane: They're gonna do a show on the slopes!
Len: <What?! A show?!>
Kohane: Yes, the ski resort we're visiting is going to be putting on a Christmas show.
Kohane: Not only that, some of the cast members from Phoenix Wonderland are going to be performing!
Rin: <Phoenix Wonderland? As in your favorite amusement park?>
Luka: <I see. That certainly explains why you're so excited!>
Kohane: Yes, and everyone from Wonderlands×Showtime is also going to be performing!
Rin: <Wonderlands×Showtime...? Oh, isn't that the troupe you're always telling us about?!>
Kohane: Yeah, I've been a huge fan ever since I first saw them perform!
Kohane: They're always putting on these really spectacular shows that put a big smile on my face!
Kohane: Not only that, the show at the ski resort is even being directed by their director, Kamishiro...!
Kohane: Which is why I can't wait...!
Len: <Whoa, I can tell...!>
An: Haha. Lately, she's been getting super excited every time we start talking about this show!
KAITO: <I see. Then, when you all go, you'll get to enjoy both skiing and this show!>
Akito: To be honest, I'm also kinda wondering exactly what kind of show they're gonna put on at a ski resort.
Toya: Indeed. This is Tsukasa's troupe we're talking about here. I'm sure that whatever they do is going to be spectacular.
Luka: <Oh, if you're all willing to say that, then I'd like to see it as well...!>
Luka: <Would it be possible for me to come watch? It sounds like a lot of fun!>
Kohane: Of course! Let's all watch it together!
Kohane: Hehe. Now I really can't wait for Christmas to come...
Toya: Me neither. However, the weather forecast for the day before we go said to expect heavy snow until around noon, which is slightly concerning...
Kohane: Wait, really?
Akito: But it should be fine as long as it's sunny the day we go, right? And we'll have plenty of powder too.
An: Right. We won't have any problems as long as we get to go skiing and see that show!
Kohane: Oh... That's true.
Akito: More importantly, have you picked which gloves you're gonna get?
Kohane: *Gasp* N-No, not yet...!
Kohane: I'll try to choose quickly since we still have a lot of shopping left to do.
An: I'll help you! Let's find you the best pair we can, Kohane!
Kohane: Thanks, An. Let's see... Which color should I get these in...?
